<subSubSection id="C37642ECFFF2FFC6FA13528B504AF48D" pageId="31" pageNumber="583" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="8BD31167FFF2FFC6FA13528B504AF48D" blockId="31.[1453,2661,1902,2921]" pageId="31" pageNumber="583">
<emphasis id="B918CD75FFF2FFC6FA13528B5D6DF537" bold="true" box="[1455,1804,2690,2723]" pageId="31" pageNumber="583">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List. Flooding from filling of the Petit Saut Dam destroyed habitat of the type locality of the Sinnamary Brush-tailed Rat in French Guiana. Additional studies on distribution, habitat, abundance, ecology, and conservation threats to Sinnamary Brush-tailed Rat are needed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
